c_shape, arc_peak_position, tempo_deviation_pct, dynamic_range_db, articulation_mean, breath_after_ms, tension_target, restraint, call_response_role)<br/>- arc_shape is one of parabolic/cosine/bezier/flat/inverted<br/>- conservative defaults: tempo_deviation_pct=4, dynamic_range_db=9, arc_peak_position=0.6, breath_after_ms=250, restraint=0.0<br/>- tests verify defaults match research-calibrated KTH k=1 values and reject out-of-range inputs |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| 31 | T-031 | Implement SectionEnvelope with breakpoint functions over tempo_base, density_target, dynamic_plane, brightness, tension_trajectory. | T1 | 3 | 3 | CCH-003 | T-001 | - `render/events.py` defines SectionEnvelope with breakpoint-function interpolation (linear default, optional spline)<br/>- envelope samples at arbitrary normalized position 0..1 within section<br/>- phrase-arc rules compose multiplicatively with section-envelope samples<br/>- tests verify interpolation, composition with phrase arcs, and parameter bounds |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| 32 | T-032 | Define IntentTag enum (build/settle/question/answer/withhold/punctuate) and require every phrase to carry one. | T1 | 3 | 3 | CCH-004 | T-001 | - IntentTag enum exists in `render/events.py` with exactly six values<br/>- composition gate rejects phrases missing intent_tag on long pieces<br/>- micro pieces may use punctuate as the default<br/>- tests verify enum completeness and gate rejection path |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| 33 | T-033 | Define Role enum (ostinato/melody/pad/perc/accent/silence) with grid_locked flag and role-filter policy used by all rules. | T1 | 6 | 3 | CCH-005 | T-001 | - Role enum exists with grid_locked boolean attribute (ostinato=True, perc=True, melody=False, pad=False, accent=False, silence=N/A)<br/>- every rule in the stack respects a shared `rule.applies_to(role)` filter so grid-locked voices skip R1–R8<br/>- tests verify grid-locked voices emerge from the render pass with timing_deviation_ms == 0 and no microtiming jitter |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| 34 | T-034 | Implement seeded-RNG architecture with per-stage sub-seeds derived from a root seed along a seed_path tuple. | T1 | 5 | 3 | CCH-006 | T-001 | - `render/seed.py` exposes derive_seed(root_seed, path_tuple) returning deterministic 32-bit sub-seed<br/>- Event.seed_path records the exact path used so any randomness inside rules can be reproduced<br/>- tests verify same (root, path) always yields same sub-seed across process restarts and Python minor versions |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| 35 | T-035 | Refactor composition stage to emit score-tree with PerformanceIntent + SectionEnvelope + IntentTag metadata, deterministic from composition seed. | T1 | 6 | 3 | CCH-007 | T-001 | - `recursive_composer.py` and `score_tree.py` extended to attach PerformanceIntent to every phrase node and SectionEnvelope to every section node<br/>- composer accepts an explicit composition_seed argument and produces byte-identical score trees for the same seed + brief<br/>- existing pieces still compose successfully; gate passes on unchanged repertoire<br/>- tests verify determinism (two runs same seed → equal score-tree hash) and metadata presence |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| 36 | T-036 | Define the OSC/SuperCollider event contract that carries full Event metadata including rule_stack provenance through to the synth. | T1 | 5 | 3 | CCH-008 | T-001 | - OSCend cache/reprobe logic only as fallback behavior instead of the primary live path.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- Brought the gallery back under the same AV boot contract as the face: the repo now ships a top-level `gallery_x11.py` entrypoint again, and `cypherclaw_av_boot.sh` now starts and deduplicates `gallery_x11.py` alongside `face_display.py` so reboot recovery cannot leave the gallery unmanaged or multiplied into dozens of stale X processes.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- Tightened the display recovery behavior again: `cypherclaw_av_boot.sh` now force-restarts `face_display.py` and `gallery_x11.py` on recovery instead of only deduplicating them, because a single stale headless display process was enough to leave the monitors blank while still looking “healthy” in `ps`.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- Fixed the display-runtime environment for those restarts too: `cypherclaw_av_boot.sh` now exports `XDG_RUNTIME_DIR=/run/user/1000` before launching face and gallery, which avoids the live SDL/X error where both display clients would restart with `DISPLAY=:0` but still fail to attach to the user session.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- Turned EMSD sample planning into real playback: added `sample_event_renderer.py`, `sample_playback_engine.py`, and `sample_status.py`; `cypherclaw_boot.sh` now starts the playback daemon; `/tmp/sample_dsp_activity.json` now feeds rendered room-derived WAV events through `pw-play`; and `/tmp/sample_playback_state.json` exposes the live sampler state for operators and face surfaces.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- Hardened the sample-playback daemon so stable ambient scenes can refresh repeatedly after cooldown instead of firing once per unchanged signature, and render failures now write a structured error state instead of crashing the loop.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- Taught `face_display.py` to surface the live EMSD sample layer from `/tmp/sample_dsp_activity.json`, so the head monitor can show which source and activity mode the room-sampling layer is currently holding or triggering.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- Rebalanced EMSD source authority toward the room in lived-in late phases: capstone `Convergence` and `Crystallization` now prefer `room_mic` outside `away_practice`, DSP scene focus follows that same room bias, and `sample_dsp_activity.py` can retarget a sparse late-phase `self_bus` request onto a fresh room capture while still preserving the original requested source in state for operator visitests/test_first_boot.py:444:        i