ported partner behaviors through `json.dumps(..., sort_keys=True)`. `tests/test_test_theramini_duet_depth.py` pins the base test file at fractal depth >= 2 and requires the named end-to-end class/method plus a machine-readable depth marker. Existing production behavior remains unchanged because the Theramini duet surface already produced meaningful one-path output; startup identity anchors remain green (`11 passed`) and the full validation gate (`4679 passed, 3 skipped`, Ruff clean, mypy clean) remains clean, and no new dependencies or migrations were introduced.
