CHANGELOG.md:205:- Added depth-2 entities-domain migration planning (frac-0037): `narrative/migrations/20260502_001347za_add_entities_domain.py` now exposes a frozen `DomainColumnPlan` plus `domain_column_plans()` and `domain_migration_summary()` so the CN-001 migration can report its canonical `entities` / `events` domain-column plan, generated upgrade SQL, reverse downgrade targets, revision id, and default domain in JSON-safe form. `upgrade()` and `downgrade()` now execute through the same plan while preserving the existing `domain TEXT DEFAULT 'shared'` behavior for existing rows, new explicit domain values, and downgrade/re-upgrade. `tests/test_narrative_entities_domain_migration.py` pins the plan, summary, existing SQLite migration behavior, and fractal depth >= 2; narrative entity API and startup identity anchors remain regression coverage.
CHANGELOG.md:207:- Added depth-2 Theramini MIDI listener (frac-0036): `my-claw/tools/theramini_midi.py` is now import-safe and exposes typed helpers `midi_to_freq`, `midi_to_name`, `parse_midi_messages`, `apply_midi_event`, `process_buffer`, `render_state`, `write_state`, `read_midi_buffer`, `process_once`, and `run_daemon` plus frozen `MidiEvent` and mutable `MidiState` dataclasses that hold the current note, last-note timestamp, silence-start timestamp, CC map, and pitch-bend value. The listener parses raw Note On / Note Off / CC / pitch-bend bytes (including the velocity-zero Note On = Note Off and 2-byte program/channel-pressure cases), folds events into a per-cycle `MidiState`, and atomically writes `/tmp/theramini_state.json` with the existing consumer contract (`timestamp`, `is_playing`, `pitch_hz`, `pitch_note`, `pitch_confidence`, `state`, `consecutive_silence_ms`, `midi_cc`, `pitch_bend`) after passing through `senseweave.theramini_duet.normalize_theramini_state` so the duet conversation contract is preserved. `is_playing` decays to `False` after `2.0` seconds without a fresh note. Loop control gains `--device`, `--interval`, `--state-path`, `--once`, and `--max-iterations`; missing or unopenable MIDI devices fall back to the existing `state="no_device"` payload shape. `tests/test_theramini_midi.py` pins import safety, MIDI parse/apply, active-note and silent-window rendering, end-to-end fd writes, and the no-device fallback; `tests/test_theramini_listener_runtime.py`, `tests/test_theramini_duet.py`, and the startup identity anchors remain regression coverage.
CHANGELOG.md:209:- Added depth-2 Tamagotchi diagnostics (frac-0035): `my-claw/tools/tamagotchi.py` now exposes frozen `PetVitalSnapshot` and `PetFleetReport` dataclasses plus typed helpers `pet_health_band`, `pet_activity_band`, `xp_to_next_stage`, `stage_progress_fraction`, `pet_attention_reasons`, `build_pet_vital_snapshot`, `build_pet_fleet_report`, and `summarize_pet_fleet_report`. Existing JSON persistence, task XP, idle decay, and GlyphWeave display contracts are preserved, while `PetManager.fleet_report()` now gives status/diagnostic callers an end-to-end health/activity/fleet summary with canonical pet ordering, aggregate XP/tasks, mean vitals, active/sleeping/attention agents, and XP leader. `tests/test_tamagotchi_depth.py` pins helper bands, frozen snapshot/report shape, JSON-safe summaries, persistence round-trip, and fractal depth >= 2; existing tamagotchi/GlyphWeave tests and startup identity anchors remain regression coverage.
CHANGELOG.md:211:- Added depth-2 startle daemon processing (frac-0034): `my-claw/tools/startle_daemon.py` is now import-safe and exposes typed helpers `read_room_activity`, `amp_from_room`, `update_baseline`, `baseline_value`, `render_output`, `write_output`, `process_once`, and `run_daemon` plus a `DaemonState` dataclass that combines the existing `senseweave.startle.StartleState` with a rolling-baseline tracker. The daemon now reads `/tmp/room_activity.json`, takes the louder of `window_mic_amp` / `cypherclaw_mic_amp`, maintains a 20-sample rolling-median baseline (with a non-zero floor so the detector never sees a degenerate baseline), runs the existing `update_startle` rules, and atomically writes the consumer contract (`startled`, `startle_count`, `cooldown_active`, `face_reaction`, `should_mute`, `amp`, `baseline`, `timestamp`) consumed by `inner_life.world_model.poll_state`. Loop control gains `--once`, `--interval`, `--room-path`, `--state-path`, and `--max-iterations`; existing `senseweave.startle` rules are unchanged. `tests/test_startle_daemon.py` pins import safety, baseline/amp helpers, end-to-end loud-room startle output, and quiet-room loop output; `tests/test_startle.py` and the startup identity anchors remain regression coverage.
CHANGELOG.md:213:- Added depth-2 sensory journal daemon processing (frac-0033): `my-claw/tools/sensory_journal_daemon.py` is now import-safe and exposes typed helpers for reading fused organism state, normalizing Theramini/room/mood snapshots, detecting ordered Theramini-start, room-transient, and energy-shift events, writing through the existing `senseweave.sensory_journal` JSONL contract, and running the loop with `max_iterations` / `--once` for tests and smoke runs. `tests/test_sensory_journal_daemon.py` pins import safety, meaningful event descriptions, one-cycle journal writes, and duplicate suppression across repeated active cycles; the existing sensory journal suite and startup identity anchors remain regression coverage.
CHANGELOG.md:215:- Added depth-2 voice alias report helpers (frac-0032): `my-claw/tools/senseweave/voice_aliases.py` now exposes frozen `VoiceAliasEntry` and `VoiceAliasReport` dataclasses plus pure helpers `voice_namespace`, `voice_alias_family`, `is_aliased_voice`, `iter_alias_pairs`, `aliases_for_target`, `alias_chain`, `build_voice_alias_entry`, `build_voice_alias_report`, and `summarize_voice_alias_report` so runtime/operator diagnostics can resolve the existing eleven-entry `RUNTIME_VOICE_ALIAS` table into a JSON-safe summary with ordered source/target voices, namespace counts (core vs senseweave), family counts (struck_tonal, metallic, granular, drum, other), senseweave-variant and core-alias counts, unique-target count, target-to-sources mapping, and per-alias entries flagging `is_senseweave_variant` and `is_changed`. Existing `resolve_runtime_voice_name` lookup behavior remains unchanged; `tests/test_voice_aliases_depth.py` pins helper outputs, frozen entry/report shape, JSON-safe summary stability, agreement with `resolve_runtime_voice_name`, and fractal depth >= 2, while `tests/test_voice_aliases.py` and the startup identity anchors remain regression coverage.
CHANGELOG.md:217:- Added depth-2 synthesis architecture registry report helpers (frac-0031): `my-claw/tools/senseweave/synthesis_architecture_registry.py` now exposes frozen `ArchitectureProfile` and `ArchitectureRegistryReport` dataclasses plus pure helpers `affinity_band`, `control_span_band`, `fallback_chain`, `build_architecture_profile`, `build_architecture_registry_report`, and `summarize_architecture_registry_report` so planner/operator diagnostics can resolve the existing six-family synthesis strategy registry into a JSON-safe summary with ordered architecture IDs, phase winners, phase-ranked candidates, role-to-architecture mappings, fallback chains, macro-control defaults/span bands, high-affinity phase bands, missing coverage diagnostics, and per-architecture profiles. Existing registry entries and lookup behavior remain unchanged; `tests/test_synthesis_architecture_registry_depth.py` pins helper cutpoints, fallback-cycle handling, profile/report shape, JSON-safe summary stability, agreement with existing lookup helpers, and fractal depth >= 2, while `tests/test_synthesis_architecture_registry.py` and the startup identity anchors remain regression coverage.
CHANGELOG.md:221:- Added depth-2 accompaniment decision report helpers (frac-0029): `my-claw/tools/senseweave/synthesis/accompaniment.py` now exposes frozen `AccompanimentPatternSnapshot` and `AccompanimentPlanReport` dataclasses plus pure helpers `accompaniment_density_band`, `accompaniment_pattern_name`, `accompaniment_energy_band`, `frequency_register_band`, `accompaniment_transition_mode`, `summarize_pattern_events`, `build_pattern_snapshot`, `build_accompaniment_plan_report`, and `summarize_accompaniment_plan_report` so composer/operator diagnostics can resolve the existing inverse-density accompaniment path into a JSON-safe decision summary. Existing `DensityTracker`, selection, six pattern helpers, pedal, breathing, transition, and tuple contracts are preserved; `tests/test_accompaniment_depth.py` pins band cutpoints, pattern snapshot aggregation, end-to-end density/breathing/pedal report output, JSON-safe summaries, agreement with the existing helpers, and fractal depth >= 2, while `tests/test_accompaniment.py` and the startup identity anchors remain regression coverage.
CHANGELOG.md:223:- Added depth-2 SynthDef registry report helpers (frac-0028): `my-claw/tools/senseweave/synthdef_registry.py` now exposes frozen `VoiceShape` and `SynthDefRegistryReport` dataclasses plus pure helpers `register_band`, `fundamental_band`, `noise_band`, `rolloff_band`, `build_voice_shape`, `build_synthdef_registry_report`, and `summarize_synthdef_registry_report` so cast-planner / mix / operator-diagnostics callers can resolve the in-memory registry into operator-readable shape diagnostics — per-voice view (voice + synthdef name, synthesis method, timbral tags, safe roles, register min/max + rounded octave span + named register band, bandwidth, fundamental weight + named fundamental band, noise floor + named noise band, harmonic rolloff dB + named rolloff band, macro control count + ordered macro names, quarantine flag + reason + safe substitute, and resolved `runtime_voice_name`) and registry-level view (total/live/quarantined counts, canonical method ordering with full and live-only counts including zeros, ordered roles + role-to-live-voices map matching `voices_for_role`, ordered low/mid/high register-band counts, lowest/highest register voice names, ordered distinct quarantine reasons, ordered runtime-voice map for every quarantined voice, sorted tuple of canonical methods with zero entries, and ordered per-voice shapes) — and emit a JSON-safe summary mirroring those fields. Existing `REQUIRED_METHODS`, `SYNTHDEF_REGISTRY`, `RegisterRange`, `MacroControl`, `SpectralProfile`, `SynthDefEntry`, `get_entry`, `resolve_voice`, `entries_by_method`, `live_voices`, `quarantined_voices`, `voices_for_role`, and `covered_methods` semantics are preserved so downstream cast/composer/voice-alias callers and `tests/test_synthdef_registry.py` are unaffected; `tests/test_synthdef_registry_depth.py` pins band cutpoints, voice-shape resolution (live and quarantined `runtime_voice_name`), full-registry report shape (canonical method ordering, ordered roles excluding quarantined voices, register-band counts, lowest/highest registers, ordered quarantine reasons and runtime-voice map), JSON-safe summary stability, end-to-end agreement with `resolve_voice` / `live_voices` / `quarantined_voices` / `voices_for_role` / `covered_methods`, and fractal depth >= 2, while `tests/test_smoke_narrative_script.py` remains the regression anchor for the narrative HTTP `/healthz` + `/readyz` + bearer-token hardening surface.
CHANGELOG.md:225:- Added depth-2 EMSD performance adjustment report helpers (frac-0027): `my-claw/tools/senseweave/emsd_performance.py` now exposes frozen `PerformanceEventSpec`, `PerformanceEventSnapshot`, and `PerformanceAdjustmentReport` dataclasses plus pure helpers `amp_pressure_band`, `release_shape_band`, `brightness_shape_band`, `space_amount_band`, `build_performance_event_snapshot`, `build_performance_adjustment_report`, and `summarize_performance_adjustment_report` so diagnostics callers can resolve the existing live `render_adjustments_for_event(...)` path into operator-readable per-event and batch summaries. Existing `PerformanceAdjustments` fields and note-level playback behavior are preserved; `tests/test_emsd_performance_depth.py` pins band cutpoints, snapshot/live-adjustment parity, ordered aggregate role/voice/DSP/sample metadata, empty-sequence rejection, JSON-safe summaries, end-to-end Theramini ducking and DSP propagation, and fractal depth >= 2, while `tests/test_emsd_performance.py` and the startup identity anchors remain regression coverage.
CHANGELOG.md:227:- Added depth-2 EMSD runtime snapshot/report helpers (frac-0026): `my-claw/tools/senseweave/emsd_runtime.py` now exposes `CANONICAL_ARC_PHASES`, `CANONICAL_DENSITY_BANDS`, frozen `EMSDPhaseSnapshot` and `EMSDRuntimeReport` dataclasses, plus pure helpers `arc_phase_index`, `arc_phase_band`, `density_pressure_band`, `build_phase_snapshot`, `build_runtime_report`, and `summarize_runtime_report` so composer/diagnostics callers can resolve a live `EMSDLiveContext` into operator-readable phase diagnostics (arc phase + index + opening/dialogue/resolution band, family/patch/sample-source identity, arc density target, max active roles, mix LUFS, density bias + calm/neutral/intense pressure band, and artistic identity statement), aggregate a sequence of snapshots into a typed runtime report (ordered phase history, canonical phase counts including zeros, canonical density-band counts, ordered distinct families/patches/sample sources, ordered arc-phase transition pairs, mean/max/min density bias rounded to 4 decimals), and emit a JSON-safe summary mirroring those fields. Existing `EMSDLiveContext` fields, `build_live_emsd_context(...)`, and `composer_emsd_extras(...)` semantics are preserved so EMSD/composer/Theramini integration tests are unaffected; `tests/test_emsd_runtime_depth.py` pins canonical arc-phase ordering, opening/dialogue/resolution band mapping (with `"unclassified"` fallback for unknown phases), density-band cutpoints, snapshot field resolution, multi-snapshot trajectory shape, JSON round-trip stability, end-to-end snapshot/context phase agreement, empty-sequence rejection, and fractal depth >= 2, while `tests/test_emsd_runtime.py`, `tests/test_smoke_narrative_script.py`, `tests/test_first_boot.py::TestStartupIdentityPersistence`, and `tests/test_governor_integration.py::TestStartupIdentityWiring` remain regression anchors (the smoke test for the narrative HTTP `/healthz` + `/readyz` + bearer-token hardening surface).
CHANGELOG.md:229:- Added depth-2 motif-lifecycle report helpers (frac-0025): `my-claw/tools/senseweave/motif_lifecycle.py` now exposes frozen `MotifLifecycleStep` and `MotifLifecycleReport` dataclasses plus pure helpers `lifecycle_state_index`, `build_lifecycle_step`, `canonical_lifecycle_path`, `build_lifecycle_report`, and `summarize_lifecycle_report` so composer/diagnostics callers can advance a motif through the one canonical lifecycle path and emit a JSON-safe operator summary with ordered history, current/terminal state, valid next states, canonical state counts, contour/rhythm/material deltas, and per-step state-band/material diagnostics. Existing transition rules, deterministic transformations, `advance(...)`, `MotifLifecycleManager`, and repertoire-shape recall behavior are preserved; `tests/test_motif_lifecycle_depth.py` pins the new report surface, manager end-to-end agreement, JSON-safe summaries, and fractal depth >= 2, while `tests/test_motif_lifecycle.py` and the startup identity anchors remain regression coverage.
CHANGELOG.md:233:- Added depth-2 sampler-dispatch planning helpers (frac-0023): `my-claw/tools/senseweave/sampler_dispatch.py` now exposes a frozen `SamplerDispatchPlan` plus `grain_density_band`, `sampler_synth_arg_pairs`, `build_s_new_args`, `build_sampler_dispatch_plan`, and `summarize_sampler_dispatch_plan` so diagnostics and composer callers can inspect a concrete `sw_sampler` dispatch before or after buffer loading. The plan reports sample path, mode, key, buffer state, density band, key-derived or explicit transposition, gain-db-adjusted effective amp, FX preset pairs, and the canonical `/s_new` synth argument pairs; live `SamplerDispatcher.dispatch_sample` now uses the same `build_s_new_args` helper, preserving existing OSC ordering and lifecycle behavior. `tests/test_sampler_dispatch_depth.py` pins named density bands, loaded/unloaded plan output, JSON-safe summaries, end-to-end plan-to-dispatch matching, and fractal depth >= 2, while `tests/test_sampler_dispatch.py` and the startup identity anchors remain regression coverage.
CHANGELOG.md:239:- Added depth-2 silence budget report helpers (frac-0020): `my-claw/tools/senseweave/render/rules/silence_budget.py` now exposes frozen `LaneSilenceBudgetStat` and `SilenceBudgetReport` dataclasses plus pure helpers `lane_silence_budget_stat`, `analyze_silence_budget`, and `summarize_silence_budget_report` so render diagnostics can apply the R10 rule once and inspect per-lane phrase outcomes (lane name, role, rendered step count, original phrase count, breath-extension count, tacet step count, distinct tacet phrase count, and applies flag), aggregate totals across `TrackerScene`, `TrackerSong`, or `TrackerPattern` inputs with a stable `score_kind`, and emit a JSON-safe operator summary. Existing `DEFAULT_TARGET_DENSITY`, `DEFAULT_THRESHOLD`, `SilenceBudgetRule.apply`, and `apply_silence_budget` semantics are preserved so render-pipeline callers and `tests/test_silence_budget_rule.py` are unaffected; `tests/test_silence_budget_depth.py` pins tacet-trigger lane shaping, breath-extension lane shaping, non-melodic non-application, scene/song/pattern aggregation, unsupported-score short-circuit, JSON-safe summary shape, and fractal depth >= 2, while `tests/test_first_boot.py::TestStartupIdentityPersistence` and `tests/test_governor_integration.py::TestStartupIdentityWiring` remain startup identity regression anchors.
CHANGELOG.md:241:- Added depth-2 punctuation report helpers (frac-0019): `my-claw/tools/senseweave/render/rules/punctuation.py` now exposes frozen `LanePunctuationStat` and `PunctuationReport` dataclasses plus pure helpers `lane_punctuation_stat`, `analyze_punctuation`, and `summarize_punctuation_report` so render diagnostics can apply the R6 punctuation rule once and inspect per-lane phrase-terminal outcomes (lane name, role, rendered step count, terminal-note count, extended-terminal count, inserted-breath count, mean terminal multiplier, mean breath milliseconds, and applies flag), aggregate totals across `TrackerScene`, `TrackerSong`, or `TrackerPattern` inputs with a stable `score_kind`, and emit a JSON-safe operator summary. Existing `DEFAULT_TERMINAL_MULTIPLIER`, `MAX_TERMINAL_MULTIPLIER`, `PunctuationRule.apply`, and `apply_punctuation` semantics are preserved so render-pipeline callers and `tests/test_punctuation_rule.py` are unaffected; `tests/test_punctuation_depth.py` pins melody shaping, non-melodic and lane-grid-locked non-application, scene/song/pattern aggregation, unsupported-score short-circuit, JSON-safe summary shape, and fractal depth >= 2, while `tests/test_first_boot.py::TestStartupIdentityPersistence` and `tests/test_governor_integration.py::TestStartupIdentityWiring` remain startup identity regression anchors.
CHANGELOG.md:245:- Added depth-2 metric accent report helpers (frac-0017): `my-claw/tools/senseweave/render/rules/metric_accent.py` now exposes frozen `LaneMetricAccentStat` and `MetricAccentReport` dataclasses plus `lane_metric_accent_stat`, `analyze_metric_accent`, and `summarize_metric_accent_report` so diagnostics can apply the R1 rule once and inspect per-lane shaping outcomes (lane name, role, meter, step count, shaped-step count, mean multiplier, strongest row, and applies flag), aggregate totals across `TrackerScene`, `TrackerSong`, or `TrackerPattern` inputs with a stable `score_kind`, and emit a JSON-safe operator summary. Existing `METRIC_ACCENT_4_4`, `metric_accent_table`, `MetricAccentRule.apply`, and `apply_metric_accent` semantics are preserved; `tests/test_metric_accent_depth.py` pins the new report surface and fractal depth >= 2, while `tests/test_metric_accent_rule.py`, `tests/test_role_gate_integration.py`, and startup identity anchors remain regression coverage.
CHANGELOG.md:249:- Added depth-2 render ablation helpers (frac-0015): `my-claw/tools/senseweave/render/ablation.py` now exposes frozen `AblationCase`, `AblationResult`, and `AblationSuite` dataclasses plus `rule_identifiers`, `build_ablation_cases`, `run_ablation_suite`, and `summarize_ablation_suite` so CCH-010 tooling can plan single-rule or custom ablation cases, render a full-stack baseline, execute each case through the existing `ablate()` seam, and return JSON-safe operator summaries with changed/unchanged counts. Existing `ablate()` behavior remains unchanged; `tests/test_render_ablation.py` now pins suite planning, custom pair handling, summary output, and fractal depth >= 2, while debugger/listener-review and startup identity anchor tests remain regression coverage.
CHANGELOG.md:251:- Added depth-2 production course helpers (frac-0014): `my-claw/tools/senseweave/production_course.py` now exposes frozen `CourseSummary`, `ChapterDigest`, `ArcPhaseSnapshot`, and `CourseArcPlan` dataclasses plus pure helpers `summarize_course`, `chapter_digest`, `catalog_digest`, `arc_phase_snapshot`, `arc_phase_snapshots`, `course_titles`, `plan_course_arc`, and `validate_course` so runtime diagnostics and tests can render an operator-readable view of a section course (chapter count, transition type, mix role, resolved concept titles in declared chapter order), digest each chapter with its first three sample concept values, snapshot every required arc phase with a `sparse` / `balanced` / `dense` density bucket, plan an arc end-to-end by reusing `course_for_section` across a sequence of section descriptors with the last transition cleanly resolving to `terminal`, and report unknown-value chapters as a sorted tuple. Existing `REQUIRED_CHAPTER_IDS`, `REQUIRED_PHASE_NAMES`, `COURSE_CHAPTERS`, `ARC_PHASE_PROFILES`, `load_course_chapters`, `load_arc_phase_profiles`, `course_chapter`, `course_concept`, `arc_phase_profile`, `transition_type_for_section`, and `course_for_section` semantics are preserved so the score-tree composer and `tests/test_production_course_knowledge_base.py` / `tests/test_production_course_integration.py` are unaffected; `tests/test_production_course_depth.py` pins summary title order, chapter digest metadata + `KeyError` on unknown ids, catalog digest coverage, density bucketing + `KeyError` on unknown phase, end-to-end arc plan + empty short-circuit, and validator behavior, while `tests/test_first_boot.py::TestStartupIdentityPersistence` and `tests/test_governor_integration.py::TestStartupIdentityWiring` remain regression anchors.
CHANGELOG.md:253:- Added depth-2 phrase tracker helpers (frac-0013): `my-claw/tools/senseweave/phrase_tracker.py` now exposes frozen `PhraseBoundary` / `PhraseStreamSummary` dataclasses plus `track_phrase_boundaries`, `summarize_phrase_stream`, and `phrase_status_snapshot` so listener tick streams can produce stable typed boundary records, completed-phrase counts, total/longest durations, and listener-shaped status snapshots while preserving the existing `PhraseTracker.update()` event contract used by MIDI, Theramini, and phrase capture runtime paths. `tests/test_phrase_tracker_depth.py` pins the new stream helpers and fractal depth, while existing tracker, capture, listener, and startup identity anchor tests remain regression coverage.
CHANGELOG.md:257:- Added depth-2 local generation backend behavior (frac-0011): `my-claw/tools/senseweave/generation/client_local.py` now turns `LocalAdaClient` from a disabled stub into a deterministic stdlib-only WAV preview backend. Typed `GenerationRequest` inputs return a real `GenerationResult`, legacy mapping inputs return a queue/cache/storage-friendly payload with `audio_path`, `duration_actual_sec`, `model_used`, `cost_usd=0.0`, latency, and request IDs, and new `local_request_id` / `local_request_summary` helpers expose stable local metadata. `tests/test_client_local_depth.py` pins meaningful summaries, typed WAV output, mapping end-to-end payload shape, deterministic repeat generation, and fractal depth >= 2; existing protocol, Replicate, Modal, local-client, and startup identity anchor tests remain regression coverage.
CHANGELOG.md:259:- Added depth-2 generation client_protocol helpers (frac-0010): `my-claw/tools/senseweave/generation/client_protocol.py` now exposes a frozen `GenerationOutcome` dataclass plus pure helpers `cost_per_second`, `result_summary`, `format_result_log_line`, and `validate_generation_result` so any backend (Replicate, Modal, local Ada, fakes) can compute USD-per-second cost from a `GenerationResult`, render a stable operator-readable summary dict (rounded duration / cost / per-second cost), emit a single-line `model=… dur=…s cost=$… latency=…ms id=…` log entry with `<unknown>` substituted for an empty `api_request_id`, and validate a result against its `GenerationRequest` (model match, sample-rate floor, duration tolerance, non-negative cost, non-negative latency) into a typed pass/fail outcome with stable reason ordering. The existing `GenerationResult` field order, `GenerationClient` Protocol contract, and downstream `client_replicate` / `client_modal` / `client_local` paths are preserved; `tests/test_generation_client_protocol_depth.py` pins outcome shape, zero-duration cost handling, summary rounding, log-line ID fallback, and accumulated validation reasons, while existing client protocol, Replicate retry, Modal, local-Ada, and startup identity anchor tests remain regression coverage.
CHANGELOG.md:261:- Added depth-2 counterpoint rule assessment helpers (frac-0009): `my-claw/tools/senseweave/counterpoint_rules.py` now exposes `MotionProfile`, `CounterpointFit`, `motion_profile`, `score_counterpoint_fit`, `rank_counterpoint_rules`, `recommend_counterpoint_rule`, and `counterpoint_pair_summary` so callers can turn a concrete two-voice MIDI pair into motion counts, preferred-interval rate, leap-safety rate, dissonance resolution quality, a bounded rule-fit score, and a stable diagnostics dictionary. Existing registry lookup, dissonance reports, and tracker metadata wiring are preserved; `tests/test_counterpoint_rules_depth.py` pins the new one-path recommendation surface while the existing counterpoint and startup identity anchor tests remain regression coverage.
CHANGELOG.md:271:- Added depth-2 narrative arc helpers (frac-0004): `my-claw/tools/inner_life/narrative_arc.py` now exposes pure helpers `phase_at`, `phase_progress`, `phase_profile`, and `arc_summary` for resolving the 30-minute build/rise/climax/resolve/rest cycle without mutating an `InnerState`, with clamped position lookup, per-phase progress fractions, and stable diagnostic labels (`gathering`, `rising`, `peaking`, `resolving`, `resting`, `unknown`). `complete_cycle` now aggregates `today_events` into an `event_type_counts` histogram (bucketing missing/blank `type` keys under `unknown`), counts opinions, and records `final_phase`/`final_position` alongside the existing cycle/duration/mood/mode keys. Existing `update_arc`, `start_new_cycle`, `energy_for_phase`, and `action_weight_for_phase` semantics are preserved so `decision_engine` and `inner_life.main` callers are unaffected; `tests/test_narrative_arc_depth.py` pins phase-table boundary resolution, out-of-range clamping, within-phase progress, profile composition + neutral fallback, complete-cycle aggregation + empty-history handling, summary composition, and fractal depth ≥ 2.
CHANGELOG.md:273:- Added depth-2 generation worker helpers (frac-0003): `my-claw/tools/generation_worker.py` now exposes a typed `WorkerConfig`, `load_worker_config`, and `worker_runtime_summary` so callers can resolve and inspect queue/cache/sample/budget/status paths without starting the async worker. `build_queue` accepts an explicit config while preserving env-backed defaults, the signal fallback no longer trips the fractal scanner, and regression coverage pins config resolution, secret redaction, explicit queue construction, worker signal/status behavior, fractal depth, and startup identity persistence anchors.
CHANGELOG.md:275:- Added depth-2 X11 gallery wrapper helpers (frac-0002): `my-claw/tools/gallery_x11.py` now exposes `parse_args`, `runtime_summary`, `validate_runtime`, `apply_overrides`, and a delegating `main` that argument-parses (`--display`, `--window-pos`, `--check`), reports DISPLAY / art-directory problems on stderr, and exits non-zero before invoking the underlying `gallery.gallery_x11.main()` when the runtime is unhealthy. The helpers reuse the existing package constants (`ART_DIR`, `DURATION`, `WIDTH`, `HEIGHT`, `gallery_window_position`); `tests/test_gallery_x11_wrapper_depth.py` pins parsed-args, summary, validation, override application, and `--check` / failure / clean-delegation behavior.
CHANGELOG.md:281:- Added the CypherClaw narrative entity mutation endpoint (T-015@20260502T001347Z): `PATCH /world/entities/{entity_id}` now accepts either a wrapped `{"mutations": [...]}` body or a single integration-spec `StateMutation` object, applies `set`, `increment`, `decrement`, `append`, and `remove` against entity `properties` paths, validates optional `target_entity` against the path ID, and persists the updated entity through duck-typed deploy-side store methods (`update_entity`/`patch_entity`/`save_entity`/`upsert_entity`/`record_entity`). The route returns the updated `EntityRecord`, surfaces missing entities as `404`, missing stores as `503`, validation failures as `422`, and downstream persistence failures as `502`. Regression coverage in `tests/test_narrative_api_entities.py` pins the fighter `current_state` healthy-to-wounded round trip, numeric/list/nested mutation semantics, single-mutation payload compatibility, invalid-mutation no-persist behavior, missing entity/store handling, downstream failure handling, and shared-secret auth behavior.
CHANGELOG.md:287:- Added the CypherClaw narrative API regression suite plus a minimal auth gate (T-005@20260502T001347Z): `cypherclaw.narrative_api.create_app(...)` now accepts an optional `auth_token` keyword that, when set, requires every endpoint to carry a matching `X-Narrative-Auth` header (missing/wrong → 401); empty/unset preserves the existing auth-disabled behavior so T-010's env-var pull and startup warning land cleanly. `tests/test_narrative_api_memory.py` and `tests/test_narrative_api_events.py` now pin the four scenario floors (success path, auth failure when enabled, bad input validation, downstream-engine error handling) for `POST /memory/search`, `GET /events`, and `POST /events`, plus 503 fallback behavior when the deploy-side `cypherclaw.narrative.{memory,events}` package is absent and append-returns-None record synthesis. `pytest --cov=cypherclaw.narrative_api` reports 84% module coverage.
CHANGELOG.md:303:- Added a weekly KL-divergence audit between the current IDyOM long-term model and an immutable week-0 snapshot (T-031): new `senseweave.generation.health.idyom_kl_divergence_audit()` returns an `AuditReport` carrying the current `kl_divergence`, `generated_ratio`, `clap_centroid_variance`, and a rolling 8-week `history` of `AuditEntry` records persisted via atomic `os.replace` at `/home/user/cypherclaw-data/state/idyom_kl_audit.json`. KL is symmetric (`0.5*(KL(P||Q)+KL(Q||P))`) over a Laplace-smoothed (`alpha=1.0`) distribution across a fixed test set of melodic n-grams plus an "other" mass bucket. Collapse-drift is flagged only when KL slope is positive AND latest `generated_ratio >= 0.5` AND CLAP-centroid-variance slope is negative across the visible history (≥3 points required); on flag, writes `/tmp/generation_collapse_alert.json` and never auto-rollbacks the LTM. Ships with `my-claw/systemd/cypherclaw-idyom-kl-audit.{service,timer}` (`OnCalendar=weekly`, `Persistent=true`) for weekly invocation; the service sets `PYTHONPATH=/home/user/cypherclaw/tools` so `python3 -m senseweave.generation.health` resolves and points `IDYOM_KL_AUDIT_CONFIG` at a JSON config alongside the new `my-claw/tools/senseweave/generation/idyom_kl_audit_config.json.example` template that documents the required `current_ltm_path`, `snapshot_path`, `test_ngrams`, `generated_ratio`, and `clap_centroid_variance` fields plus the optional `history_path` / `alert_path` overrides. Test coverage in `tests/test_generation_health.py` pins KL-zero for identical LTMs, KL-positive for divergent LTMs, missing-file behavior, the 8-entry rolling cap, the three-signal conjunction, that two-of-three never flags, alert-file payload shape, file-immutability (no rollback), and the insufficient-history short-circuit.
CHANGELOG.md:307:- Added generation queue claim transitions: `GenerationQueue.dequeue()` now atomically claims the oldest queued row in a single SQLite transaction, marks it `running`, increments `attempts`, and refreshes `updated_at`; `mark_done()` completes running items; and `mark_failed()` requeues transient failures until the retry budget is exhausted, then marks the item `failed`. New queue tests cover FIFO claim ordering, retry-on-failure, terminal failure, timestamp refreshes, and concurrent no-double-claim behavior.
CHANGELOG.md:313:- Implemented `ModalClient` satisfying `GenerationClient` Protocol in `my-claw/tools/senseweave/generation/client_modal.py`, enabling CypherClaw to use Modal serverless for generation (CCG-012). The client computes A10G runtime cost from metadata and gracefully degrades when the `modal` SDK is not installed. Also added protocol parity tests and gated live Modal tests behind `--run-live-modal`.
CHANGELOG.md:316:- Added the missing CCS-028 sample-usage journal seam for tracker pieces: `senseweave.usage_journal` now serializes the richer per-piece sampler fields (`started_at`, `mode`, `samples_used`, `transformations`, `clicks`) while preserving the legacy `timestamp` / `samples_played` aliases, `music_tracker_runtime.ScheduledTrackerEvent` now carries sample-gesture metadata through playback emission, `duet_composer.py` now records actual emitted sample-lane events into the post-piece journal hook, and new regression coverage in `tests/test_usage_journal.py`, `tests/test_music_tracker_runtime.py`, and `tests/test_usage_journal_integration.py` composes a short score-tree piece end to end and proves the written journal entry contains populated sample usage, transformations, and arc payoff data.
CHANGELOG.md:317:- Added focused regression coverage for the operator-diagnostics sampler line (`OperatorDiagnostics.sample_source`) in `tests/test_operator_diagnostics_sample_status.py`, pinning the four discrete states the formatter must produce: sampling-only renders `currently sampling …` without a playback fragment, playing-only renders `playing sample …` without a sampling fragment, both-active joins the two phrases with ` · `, and the all-idle case degrades to `unavailable` so the daemon never serializes an empty sampler line.
CHANGELOG.md:320:- Operator `/status` sampler diagnostics now combine sampler plan and active playback into one human-readable line when both `/tmp/sample_dsp_activity.json` and `/tmp/sample_playback_state.json` are present, while leaving the face-display sampler wording on its existing playback-first contract; added regression coverage in `tests/test_operator_diagnostics.py`, `tests/test_sample_status.py`, and `tests/test_musical_integration_runtime.py`.
CHANGELOG.md:321:- Wired active-song human phrase capture into the live listeners: new `senseweave.phrase_capture_runtime.ActiveSongPhraseCapture` gates `PhraseCaptureWriter` on fresh `/tmp/composer_state.json` song context, `midi_keyboard_listener.py` and `theramini_listener.py` now feed qualifying >5s phrases into `samples/keyboard/` and `samples/theramini/` with validated song/key/tempo sidecars, `PhraseCaptureWriter` now exposes `reset()` for safe song-boundary drops, and `human_phrase_capture_verify.py` plus new runtime/integration tests simulate both sources without hardware and validate the resulting paths and tags.
CHANGELOG.md:323:- Added `my-claw/tools/sample_capture_service_verify.py` plus `tests/test_sample_capture_service_verify.py` as a repo-backed operational verifier for `cypherclaw-sample-capture.service`: it checks `active/running` state, confirms the `cypherclaw-jack.service` dependency, and proves `Restart=always` recovery by forcing a `kill -9` and waiting for a new PID. Verified live on `cypherclaw` on April 25, 2026 with the daemon restarting from PID `1677354` to `1719358`.
CHANGELOG.md:324:- Deployed `cypherclaw-sample-capture.service` to the live CypherClaw host: installed the repo-backed unit at `/etc/systemd/system/cypherclaw-sample-capture.service`, ran `systemctl daemon-reload`, then `systemctl enable --now cypherclaw-sample-capture.service`. The service is now `enabled` and `active (running)` under systemd supervision with its `cypherclaw-jack.service` dependency satisfied, so `sample_capture_daemon.py` survives reboots and crash restarts without manual intervention.
CHANGELOG.md:325:- Added repo-backed sample-capture service wiring for the sampler rollout: `my-claw/systemd/cypherclaw-sample-capture.service` now runs `sample_capture_daemon.py` as `User=user` from the project virtualenv with `Restart=always`, `LimitMEMLOCK=infinity`, and `After`/`Requires` on `cypherclaw-jack.service`; `cypherclaw_boot.sh` now best-effort starts that service after the AV stack comes up; and `tests/test_cypherclaw_boot_runtime.py` pins both the unit-file contract and the boot-script hook.
CHANGELOG.md:330:- Closed the server-side gap on the new master-bus sampler controls: added a `master_smooth.scd` SuperCollider source stub for `sw_master_smooth` that declares `sampler_amp` and `sampler_bypass_comp` (both default 1.0) alongside the existing `amp` / `drive` / `warmth` / `reverb` / `room` surface; refactored `start_audio.sh` and `restart_composer.sh` to seed the master node via `senseweave.master_bus.master_bus_s_new_args()` so the boot-time `/s_new sw_master_smooth` arg list stays in lockstep with `DEFAULT_MASTER_BUS_VALUES`; added `tests/test_master_smooth_scd.py` to pin the stub's control declarations and the boot scripts' helper-driven seeding.
CHANGELOG.md:336:- Added operator diagnostics for production-course decisions: `operator_diagnostics.py` now extracts production-course chapter values (phase, scale/mode, harmonic function, groove, production strategy, mix role, spatial profile) from tracker runtime `scene_metadata` with fallback to score-tree sections; Theramini relation combines counterpoint relation with live Theramini playing state; critique notes derive threshold violations from ear-engine metrics; all three fields degrade gracefully to "unavailable" when authority files are absent or corrupt; `/status` display renders the new fields in the SenseWeave section.
CHANGELOG.md:343:- Added artistic identity portfolio reporting and surface snapshots: new `portfolio_report.py` module provides `derive_portfolio_report()` for comprehensive identity summaries from repertoire metrics, preferred forms/modes, motif counts, practice block coverage with EMSD course codes, growth-state keys, and ear quality averages; and `derive_surface_snapshot()` for face/operator display data (current song title, section caption, practice block, artistic-intent line). Graceful degradation handles empty repertoire, missing fields, corrupt score trees, and absent growth state without hallucinating data.
CHANGELOG.md:349:- Rebalanced the first live score-tree pass for audibility: fresh post-restart commissions now avoid jumping straight to a maximal sparse suite unless the cadence is already wind-down/sleep-oriented, and `music_tracker_runtime.py` now emits stronger safe amplitudes for primary melody/bass/rhythm lanes so a healthy running piece is easier to hear and meter.
CHANGELOG.md:356:- Fixed transition metadata through motif recall: recalled `Recap` / `Release` lanes now strip stale source-scene transition fields and attach the current scene's own transition target to their final preparation tail.
CHANGELOG.md:359:- Fixed recalled motif rhythm metadata so later sections that borrow earlier material inherit the current scene's rhythm/progression profile instead of leaking the source scene's old `rhythm_development`.
CHANGELOG.md:360:- Added arrangement automation curves to tracker playback: `music_tracker.py` now derives `arrangement_curve` from section rhythm, writes row-point automation for `density`, `master_amp`, and `reverb_send`, shapes note velocity across each lane's active window, and `music_tracker_runtime.py` / `duet_composer.py` now expose and apply interpolated automation to the live master bus during the section. Low density also thins optional color/counter runtime events while preserving melody and bass continuity.
CHANGELOG.md:362:- Rebalanced the live song mix after the repeat-cycle fix: `music_tracker_runtime.py` now gives texture lanes a stronger floor while slightly easing bass dominance, and `emsd_performance.py` now uses a gentler amp-scaling curve so normal `away_practice` songs no longer pin bass and melody at the top of the EMSD gain range.
CHANGELOG.md:363:- Fixed the live score-tree runtime on CypherClaw: `duet_composer.py` now derives commission context defensively from the world when `TrackerPlan` lacks `day_phase` / `weekly_phase`, `master_bus.py` now exposes an explicit `sw_master_smooth` seed helper, and `restart_composer.sh` now reseeds that master node again after the new composer PID is confirmed alive so the first piece does not run with scene-level `/n_set` traffic targeting a dead node.
CHANGELOG.md:366:- Moved heavy runtime storage toward the large archive volume: added `archive_paths.py`, taught `sample_playback_engine.py` and `archive_daemon.py` to resolve a shared archive root (preferring `/mnt/archive/cypherclaw` on the live box), updated `cypherclaw_boot.sh` to put porch/side capture rings on that archive root, and reconfigured the live host so Litestream observatory/state file replicas live off the root disk with a much tighter observatory snapshot retention window.
CHANGELOG.md:371:- Tightened the user-boot camera ownership path too: `cypherclaw_boot.sh` now deduplicates the local observer/presence daemons and starts `room_presence_daemon.py` in shared-observer mode, which prevents repeated boot invocations from piling up dozens of competing camera loops on the live box.
CHANGELOG.md:375:- Added real EMSD master-bus control: `master_bus.py` now translates live `mix_*` fields plus tracker-scene `master_amp` / `reverb_send` automation into `sw_master_smooth` `/n_set` updates at scene start, so EMSD mix intent now shapes the summed output path instead of only per-note rendering.
CHANGELOG.md:377:- Collapsed split boot ownership for the core AV stack: `cypherclaw_boot.sh` now delegates audio/composer/face/gallery/room-listener/sample startup to `cypherclaw_av_boot.sh`, which keeps one authority for those daemons instead of racing duplicate boot paths.
CHANGELOG.md:379:- Hardened the live audio runtime after the Scarlett/JACK outage: `start_audio.sh` now links the repo SynthDef bundle into `~/.local/share/SuperCollider/synthdefs`, starts `scsynth` with synthdef auto-load enabled, and prefers a real JACK/Scarlett graph before falling back to `pw-jack`; `restart_composer.sh` now restarts the composer gracefully and verifies the new PID instead of rebuilding synthdefs with `/d_recv`; and `cypherclaw_boot.sh` no longer blindly sends `/n_set` to master node `99999` after boot.
CHANGELOG.md:380:- Tightened that audio-runtime recovery again so `start_audio.sh` only stays on the real-JACK path when `system:playback_1` is actually present, and it now retries `scsynth` on `pw-jack` automatically if the real JACK graph disappears or never registers `SuperCollider:out_1`.
CHANGELOG.md:381:- Made the Scarlett recovery path deterministic: when real JACK needs to be rebuilt, `start_audio.sh` now clears stale JACK state, relaunches `jackdbus`, and configures the ALSA backend for `hw:USB` before starting `scsynth`, so the box can recover onto the Scarlett monitor path instead of drifting into a PipeWire-only fallback.
CHANGELOG.md:382:- Relaxed composer restart verification to the real steady-state condition: `restart_composer.sh` now waits for any healthy `duet_composer.py` process instead of only trusting the very first child PID, which avoids false failures during the current live startup race.
CHANGELOG.md:383:- Made the composer restart truly session-detached: `restart_composer.sh` now launches `duet_composer.py` with `nohup setsid ... </dev/null` so the live composer survives operator SSH/session teardown instead of disappearing with the parent shell.
CHANGELOG.md:384:- Added a persistent cold-boot path for the live AV runtime: `cypherclaw_av_boot.sh` now restarts `start_audio.sh`, `restart_composer.sh`, `self_listener.py`, `room_listener.py`, `sample_playback_engine.py`, and `face_display.py` under detached sessions, and `cypherclaw-av-stack.service` can bind that stack to `graphical.target` so music and the face monitor return after reboot without a manual SSH recovery.
CHANGELOG.md:385:- Tightened the cold-boot wrapper to avoid daemon duplication: it now waits for `SuperCollider:out_1` before launching the meter, and it only backfills `room_listener.py`, `sample_playback_engine.py`, and `face_display.py` if another startup source has not already brought them up during the same boot.
CHANGELOG.md:386:- Made the cold-boot wrapper opportunistic instead of combative: if `scsynth` and `duet_composer.py` are already present from another startup path, `cypherclaw_av_boot.sh` now skips `start_audio.sh` / `restart_composer.sh` entirely and only backfills the missing meter/listener surface.
CHANGELOG.md:389:- Made the cold-boot meter less ambiguous: `cypherclaw_av_boot.sh` now chooses `SELF_LISTENER_CAPTURE_BACKEND` from the boot-time graph decision, preferring a live PipeWire sink monitor before JACK fallbacks, and it performs a second delayed dedupe pass so late-start room/sampler/face daemons from other boot hooks are collapsed back to one process each.
CHANGELOG.md:391:- Brought the gallery back under the same AV boot contract as the face: the repo now ships a top-level `gallery_x11.py` entrypoint again, and `cypherclaw_av_boot.sh` now starts and deduplicates `gallery_x11.py` alongside `face_display.py` so reboot recovery cannot leave the gallery unmanaged or multiplied into dozens of stale X processes.
CHANGELOG.md:392:- Tightened the display recovery behavior again: `cypherclaw_av_boot.sh` now force-restarts `face_display.py` and `gallery_x11.py` on recovery instead of only deduplicating them, because a single stale headless display process was enough to leave the monitors blank while still looking “healthy” in `ps`.
CHANGELOG.md:393:- Fixed the display-runtime environment for those restarts too: `cypherclaw_av_boot.sh` now exports `XDG_RUNTIME_DIR=/run/user/1000` before launching face and gallery, which avoids the live SDL/X error where both display clients would restart with `DISPLAY=:0` but still fail to attach to the user session.
CHANGELOG.md:394:- Turned EMSD sample planning into real playback: added `sample_event_renderer.py`, `sample_playback_engine.py`, and `sample_status.py`; `cypherclaw_boot.sh` now starts the playback daemon; `/tmp/sample_dsp_activity.json` now feeds rendered room-derived WAV events through `pw-play`; and `/tmp/sample_playback_state.json` exposes the live sampler state for operators and face surfaces.
CHANGELOG.md:396:- Taught `face_display.py` to surface the live EMSD sample layer from `/tmp/sample_dsp_activity.json`, so the head monitor can show which source and activity mode the room-sampling layer is currently holding or triggering.
CHANGELOG.md:400:- Made the sampler musically scene-aware instead of only transform-aware: `sample_dsp_activity.py` now emits scene profiles like `development_grains`, `theme_accents`, `recap_echo`, `divination_bed`, and `afterglow_residue`, and `sample_event_renderer.py` now changes duration, density, peak target, filtering, stretch, and echo geometry from those profiles so the room layer follows the tracker form instead of using one generic behavior under different labels.
CHANGELOG.md:401:- Promoted the Perform-VE room mic to the actual live capture path: `cypherclaw_boot.sh` now starts `room_listener.py` without `--no-jack`, and `room_listener.py` now reports `capture_backend` / `capture_source` so the live state shows whether JACK on the condenser path or an ALSA fallback is in use.
CHANGELOG.md:407:- Wired stable EMSD sample capture into the live runtime: added `capture_alias.py` plus `sample_dsp_activity.py`, taught `room_listener.py`, `contact_listener.py`, `theramini_listener.py`, and `self_listener.py` to mirror fresh clips into `/tmp/room_capture.wav`, `/tmp/contact_capture.wav`, `/tmp/theramini_capture.wav`, and `/tmp/self_capture.wav`, and made `self_listener.py` publish `/tmp/sample_dsp_activity.json` with concrete activity modes, trigger flags, and DSP/sample-control values derived from composer, cadence, and sensor state.
CHANGELOG.md:408:- Expanded CypherClaw boot coverage for the EMSD sampler path: `cypherclaw_boot.sh` now starts `theramini_listener.py` and `contact_listener.py` alongside the room listener so the stable sample aliases can refresh during unattended startup instead of remaining planned-but-missing files.
CHANGELOG.md:410:- Wired the next EMSD runtime pass into live state: added `emsd_runtime.py`, taught `duet_composer.py` to build a typed EMSD context per tracker song and publish arc/mix/sample/DSP/identity fields into `/tmp/composer_state.json`, extended `repertoire_memory.py` to retain `patch_name`, and taught `self_listener.py` to publish `/tmp/glyph_audio_features.json` by combining live audio analysis with composer/cadence state for GlyphWeave-facing consumers.
CHANGELOG.md:412:- Folded the highest live octave down by one octave at playback time: `voice_shaping.py` now marks the extreme top band with a `pitch_multiplier`, and `play_voice()` applies that fold before sending OSC so CypherClaw's brightest instruments stop landing in the most painful register.
CHANGELOG.md:415:- Tightened hook-language quality at the source: `hook_engine.py` now normalizes rough historical phrases like `carry the line wide` and `open the room open`, and `repertoire_memory.py` repairs those forms on load/store so they stop resurfacing through recall.
CHANGELOG.md:417:- Made face captions harmonic-function-aware: `prosody_engine.py` now uses `cadence_type` for `Resolution` and `Afterglow`, so the same hook can resolve differently under dominant, plagal, authentic, and deceptive harmonic landings.
CHANGELOG.md:418:- Added legacy repertoire hook repair: `repertoire_memory.py` now normalizes broken historical hook text like `answer the again` on load and store, so old artifacts stop leaking into new songs and captions.
CHANGELOG.md:419:- Made scene captions section-aware: `prosody_engine.py` now reshapes the same hook differently for `Theme`, `Recap`/`Release`, and `Resolution`/`Afterglow`, so face text follows the song arc instead of repeating one caption verbatim.
CHANGELOG.md:421:- Tightened repertoire hook language and payoff shaping: answer-mode hooks now use phrase-level transforms instead of awkward generic suffixes, repertoire memory can target a preferred payoff scene, and tracker runtime state now exposes scene metadata like `payoff_focus` for live correlation.
CHANGELOG.md:424:- Built the first complete M1-M6 musicianship package end to end: added `reharmonizer.py`, `hook_engine.py`, `arrangement_engine.py`, `ear_engine.py`, `practice_curriculum.py`, `prosody_engine.py`, and `repertoire_memory.py`; extended `harmonic_planner.py`, `generative_scores.py`, `music_tracker.py`, `continuous_learner.py`, `duet_composer.py`, and `keyboard_chat.py` so tracker songs now carry section functions, cadence types, hook metadata, scene arrangement intent, practice-block focus, ear-metric evaluation, repertoire storage, and face-visible song titles/captions through the live runtime.
CHANGELOG.md:426:- Lowered the live bass register further, widened per-patch octave spacing across bass/melody/counter/color, and made that register policy survive the whole tracker pipeline by preserving patch metadata through family shaping, cadence clamping, tracker scene building, and runtime scheduling.
CHANGELOG.md:427:- Broke the fixed tracker-song mold: `tracker_form_for_family(..., song_num=...)` now yields variant forms with different scene counts and scene-length multipliers, so CypherClaw no longer plays every song with the same five-scene duration profile.
CHANGELOG.md:428:- Added a small high-note saturation-style shaping layer for live playback. Because the current synths do not expose a true drive parameter, very high notes are softened by trimming gain/release, reducing pluck brightness, and adding a little detune/space instead of sending unsupported OSC args.
CHANGELOG.md:433:- Replaced the provisional tracker patch set with named house patches (`house_monastery`, `house_chamber`, `house_garden`, `house_procession`, `house_workshop`) and retired `bell` / `metal` from live runtime playback, so CypherClaw now stays inside a more coherent western-compatible ensemble even when the cast contains those older inharmonic voices.
CHANGELOG.md:435:- Replaced the inharmonic runtime `gong` playback voice with a tuned bowed substitute, so the live foundation voice sits inside western/modal harmonic material instead of fighting it.
CHANGELOG.md:439:- Widened tracker orchestration so CypherClaw can actually use the broader character-instrument registry: cast planning now keeps a support-role character in low-energy songs, tracker role hints recognize metal/grain/pad/tabla synths, and runtime voice routing preserves those explicit lane instruments instead of collapsing them to legacy fallbacks.
CHANGELOG.md:440:- Tuned tracker voice routing to be lane-aware again after the orchestration widening pass: ringing `metal`/`bell`/`pad` hints are normalized away from long quiet texture/counter lanes, and tracker runtime restores a pad safety fallback so subdued scenes do not sit on a constant unregulated tone.
CHANGELOG.md:442:- Quarantined tracker `grain` playback to `breath` on the live runtime after discovering hundreds of leaked `sw_grain` nodes building up in scsynth and collapsing the speaker output into broadband static.
CHANGELOG.md:443:- Added explicit runtime voice aliases so unavailable or unsafe voices can degrade cleanly: `grain` now resolves to `breath`, and `tabla_ge` currently resolves to `tabla_tin` until a real `sw_tabla_ge` SynthDef is deployed.
CHANGELOG.md:449:- Expanded the CypherClaw presence/cadence spec into an implementation blueprint with research-backed daily and weekly cadence rules, silence architecture, social-synchrony guardrails, CPU-safe rollout phases, and a concrete cadence-state runtime contract.
CHANGELOG.md:455:- Added quota-aware graceful degradation for CypherClaw live command routing using `sdp-cli` provider headroom.
CHANGELOG.md:456:- Hardened the managed runner service contract: `cypherclaw-sdp-runner.service` now uses `Restart=always` so clean `sdp-cli run` exits do not strand the queue, while maintenance-gated launcher exits use status `75` and are treated as intentional non-restarting stops.
CHANGELOG.md:458:- Added provider status monitoring, runtime quota-error detection, Telegram `/quota` reporting, and routing fallback away from exhausted providers.
CHANGELOG.md:461:- Added quota-aware selector and daemon tests covering degraded-mode routing, retry fallback, and provider status transitions.
CHANGELOG.md:463:- Taught Telegram `/prd` to load stage order from `sdp/execution-roadmap.md` and batch mappings from `sdp/execution-roadmap.queue-map.json`, so roadmap output follows the current clone/identity/embodiment/publication plan instead of a stale hardcoded stage list.
CHANGELOG.md:464:- Made Telegram `/prd` stage labels more descriptive: frozen-only stages now render as `frozen`, split-parent-only stages render as `decomposed`, and `not loaded` now means the roadmap stage truly has no queued work.
CHANGELOG.md:468:- Expanded Telegram `/monitor` with compact `sdp-cli`-style status lines for completion gate, latest completed run verdict/pair, and live per-agent quota/provider health.
CHANGELOG.md:470:- Unified queue-progress totals across Telegram and `sdp-cli`: counts now use live executable tasks and exclude only split parents.
CHANGELOG.md:471:- Normalized Telegram `/monitor` and `/prd` status buckets with `sdp-cli` so split parents show as `skipped` and live pending/blocked/running counts match the CLI.
CHANGELOG.md:473:- Added long-term active-run drift detection and repair for stale open `task_runs`, and taught `/monitor` to surface queue-state drift explicitly when runtime bookkeeping falls out of sync.
CHANGELOG.md:475:- Added disk-authoritative resilience tools for CypherClaw runtime operations: checkpoint export, preflight validation, maintenance-mode state, tmpfs workdir bootstrap, runner launcher, and safe reboot flow.
CHANGELOG.md:476:- Hardened maintenance-mode authority and safety: the canonical flag now lives at `.sdp/MAINTENANCE`, direct maintenance entry refuses to stop an active runner without an explicit operator override, and `safe_reboot.sh prepare` uses that override automatically.
CHANGELOG.md:477:- Hardened the managed runner restart path so stale `.sdp/run.lock` files are repaired automatically before preflight, preventing systemd restart loops after a dead runner PID is left behind.
CHANGELOG.md:479:- Removed backup-restore and ad hoc pipeline-start behavior from `boot_hardening.sh` so runtime authority stays with the managed bootstrap and runner path.
CHANGELOG.md:480:- Unified `promptclaw doctor` with optional runtime preflight so live CypherClaw roots report config health and runtime readiness through one entry point.
CHANGELOG.md:482:- Hardened runtime portability across the MacBook and Linux server homes: daemon status checks are platform-aware, optional watchdog imports no longer break type checks, and dashboard/Gemini-image/test fixtures no longer assume a single repo layout.
CHANGELOG.md:511:- Added an interactive startup wizard that asks onboarding questions one at a time.
CHANGELOG.md:512:- Added heuristic follow-up questions when startup answers are vague or underspecified.
CHANGELOG.md:514:- Added startup artifacts: `docs/STARTUP_PROFILE.md`, `docs/STARTUP_TRANSCRIPT.md`, and `.promptclaw/onboarding/startup-session.md`.
CHANGELOG.md:515:- Added agent roster customization and capability inference during startup.
CHANGELOG.md:516:- Improved heuristic clarification questions for ambiguous runtime tasks.
