specs/t-021@20260416t054258z-spec.md:5:CypherClaw's harmonic and melodic generation currently relies heavily on Western diatonic, modal, and symmetric scales. To expand the expressive range into avant-garde, ambient, and modern contemporary spaces, the system needs post-tonal, spectral, and microtonal material strategies. This allows the composer to generate pitch-class sets, harmony derived from the harmonic series (spectralism), just-intonation ratios, and 24-TET (quarter-tone) events. Additionally, SenseWeave's listening capabilities should include spectral analysis to extract prominent frequencies from the environment to seed this harmonic material.
